cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper focuses on the development of a system for computing robust suction grasp targets for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes deep learning techniques, specifically a convolutional neural network (cs.CV), to classify suction targets in point clouds. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and characterizing grasps, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the system on a physical robot, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
